  "epitaph": "A mirror for the switch, a cleaner way to count the states,\nReflective elegance now bound by C\u2019s cold fates.\nThe compiler rests, no longer wise to what the enum declares,\nAbandoned to the silence of two thousand days.\nRead-only memory holds the ghost of perfect logic in its cells,\nRest in /dev/null, wise_enum.",
